# AERAS Mosquitto ACL Configuration
# Format: topic [read|write|readwrite] <topic>

# Driver DRV-0423 Permissions
user driver_DRV-0423
topic write aeras/driver/DRV-0423/+
topic read aeras/block/+/request
topic read aeras/driver/DRV-0423/+
topic write aeras/system/heartbeat

# Block BLK-001 Permissions
user block_BLK-001
topic write aeras/block/BLK-001/request
topic write aeras/block/BLK-001/trip/+
topic read aeras/block/BLK-001/+
topic read aeras/driver/+/trip/status

# Admin ADM-001 Permissions
user admin_ADM-001
topic write aeras/admin/ADM-001/commands
topic write aeras/admin/broadcast
topic read aeras/+/+/+

# System Service Permissions
user system
topic write aeras/driver/+/points
topic write aeras/system/+
topic read aeras/+/+/+

# Pattern-based ACL (for dynamic driver/block IDs)
# Note: Mosquitto doesn't support wildcards in ACL directly,
# so you'll need to add entries for each device or use a plugin

